  "title": "Statistics: sensitivity, specificity, predictive values and likelihood ratio's",
  "body_html": "<div>A = True Positive<br />B = False Positive<br />C = False Negative<br />D = True Negative<br /><br /><div class=\"table-responsive\"><table class = \"tlarge table table-striped table-bordered\"  data-role=\"table\" id=\"tableid1\" ><thead><tr><th><b></b></th><th>Condition Positive</th><th>Condition Negative</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><b>Test Outcome Positive</b></td><td>A</td><td>B</td></tr><tr><td><b>Test Outcome Negative</b></td><td>C</td><td>D</td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><b>Sensitivity</b><br />Definition: The ability of a test to correctly identify those with the disease (true positives).<br />Formula:<br />Sensitivity = A / (A + C)<br />= True Positives / All with disease<br /><br /><b>Specificity</b><br />Definition: The ability of a test to correctly identify those without the disease (true negatives).<br />Formula:<br />Specificity = D / (B + D)<br />= True Negatives / All without disease<br /><br /><b>Positive Predictive Value (PPV)</b><br />Definition: The probability that a person with a positive test result actually has the disease.<br />Formula:<br />PPV = A / (A + B)<br />= True Positives / All positive test results<br /><br /><b>Negative Predictive Value (NPV)</b><br />Definition: The probability that a person with a negative test result truly does not have the disease.<br />Formula:<br />NPV = D / (C + D)<br />= True Negatives / All negative test results<br /><br /><b>Likelihood Ratios</b><br />Positive Likelihood Ratio (LR+)<br />LR+ = Sensitivity / (1 \u2212 Specificity)<br /><br />Negative Likelihood Ratio (LR\u2212)<br />LR\u2212 = (1 \u2212 Sensitivity) / Specificity</div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodylinks\"><table style='width:100%'><tr><td>BJA</td><td style = \"float: right;width:115px;\"><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_like_864\" data-linkid=\"864\" data-rating=\"1\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-up\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_good_count_864\" class = \"link_good_count\" style=\"color:green; font-size:85%;\">1</span><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_dislike_864\" data-linkid=\"864\" data-rating=\"0\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-down\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-down\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_bad_count_864\" class = \"link_bad_count\" style=\"color:red; font-size:85%;\">0</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.bjaed.org/article/S1743-1816(17)30457-2/fulltext\">Clinical tests: sensitivity and specificity</a></td></tr></table></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodymedia\"><table><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"#\" class=\"media_link\" data-url=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/psELBu7muNY?si=SlKISAU_lDkSahzs\" data-description=\"Sensitivity and specificity simplified\" data-media=\"144\"><img border=\"0\" alt=\"YouTube\" src=\"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/psELBu7muNY/maxresdefault.jpg\" style=\"max-width:150px;\"></a></td></tr><tr ><td style=\"padding-top:10px\" colspan=\"2\"><a style=\"\" href=\"#\" class=\"media_link\" data-url=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/psELBu7muNY?si=SlKISAU_lDkSahzs\" data-media=\"144\">Sensitivity and specificity simplified</a></td></tr><tr><td><span ><small>Let's Learn Public Health - YouTube</small></span></td><td style = \"float: right;width:115px;\"><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"media_like_180\" data-mediaid=\"180\" data-rating=\"1\" class=\"rate-media btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-up\"/></svg></button><span id=\"media_good_count_180\" class = \"media_good_count\" style=\"color:green; font-size:85%;\">0</span><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"media_dislike_180\" data-mediaid=\"180\" data-rating=\"0\" class=\"rate-media btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-down\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-